Here’s a ready-made devcontainer.json for your Codespace that comes with Rust (rustc, Cargo), Node.js, and Docker so you don’t have to reinstall tools every time.


---

Steps:

1. Inside your repo, create the folder:



mkdir -p .devcontainer

2. Create the file .devcontainer/devcontainer.json with this content:



{
  "name": "Rust + Node + Docker Dev",
  "image": "mcr.microsoft.com/devcontainers/rust:latest",

  "features": {
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/node:1": {
      "version": "lts"
    },
    "ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/docker-in-docker:2": {
      "version": "latest"
    }
  },

  "customizations": {
    "vscode": {
      "extensions": [
        "rust-lang.rust-analyzer",
        "ms-azuretools.vscode-docker",
        "ms-vscode.cpptools",
        "esbenp.prettier-vscode"
      ]
    }
  },

  "remoteUser": "vscode",

  "postCreateCommand": "rustc --version && cargo --version && node --version && npm --version",

  "mounts": [
    "source=/var/run/docker.sock,target=/var/run/docker.sock,type=bind"
  ]
}

3. Commit and push:



git add .devcontainer
git commit -m "Add full Rust + Node + Docker devcontainer"
git push

4. Close your Codespace and reopen it. It will now:

Preinstall Rust, Cargo, Node.js, and Docker tools

Auto-load Rust each session (no source $HOME/.cargo/env)

Be ready to run containers inside your Codespace.

